The lemma `indepFun_rewardByCount_Iic` asserts that the reward received at the `(n+1)`-th pull of action `a` is independent of the vector of rewards received at the `0`-th to `n`-th pulls of `a`. In the stationary environment constructed via a stream, the reward at the `k`-th pull corresponds to the `(k-1)`-th value in the i.i.d. reward stream for arm `a`. The stream values are independent by definition. We use the lemma `rewardByCount_ae_eq_stream_apply` (which relates `rewardByCount` to the stream) and the independence of the stream components.

```lean
lemma indepFun_rewardByCount_Iic [StandardBorelSpace Ω] [Nonempty Ω] [Countable α]
    (h : IsAlgEnvSeq A R alg (stationaryEnv ν) P) (a : α)
    (n : ℕ) :
    (rewardByCount A R a (n + 1)) ⟂ᵢ[𝔓'] fun ω (i : Iic n) ↦ rewardByCount A R a i ω := by
  have h_eq : rewardByCount A R a (n + 1) =ᵐ[𝔓'] fun ω ↦ ω.2 n a :=
    rewardByCount_ae_eq_stream_apply h a (n + 1) n.succ_ne_zero
  have h_vec : (fun ω (i : Iic n) ↦ rewardByCount A R a i ω) =ᵐ[𝔓']
      fun ω (i : Iic n) ↦ if i.1 = 0 then 0 else ω.2 (i.1 - 1) a := by
    rw [ae_all_iff]
    intro ⟨i, hi⟩
    by_cases h0 : i = 0
    · simp [h0, rewardByCount_zero]
    · filter_upwards [rewardByCount_ae_eq_stream_apply h a i h0] with ω hω
      simp [h0, hω]
  refine IndepFun.congr h_eq h_vec ?_
  have h_indep : iIndepFun (fun _ ↦ mα) (fun k ω ↦ ω.2 k a) 𝔓' :=
    iIndepFun_eval_eval_id_streamMeasure ν a
  exact h_indep.indepFun_finset (fun i (hi : i ∈ Iic n) ↦ if i = 0 then 0 else i - 1)
    (fun i hi ↦ by
      dsimp
      split_ifs with h0
      · simp [h0]
      · simp only [mem_Iic] at hi
        omega)
```
